President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Kansas due to severe winter storms and straight-line winds that occurred from March 17 to March 22, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. DuWayne Tewes has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.